  "prompt": "How are movies dubbed in different languages? How come we hear the same voice in the next part of the movie even after years?",
  "response": "Dubbing movies involves several steps and techniques:\n\n1. Translation Process:\n- Translators first create a script that matches the original dialogue's meaning and lip movements\n- They adapt cultural references and humor to make it relatable to the target audience\n\n2. Voice Acting:\n- Professional voice actors (dubbers) are hired to replace the original actors' voices\n- They try to match the original actor's tone, emotion, and speaking style\n- Many countries have specialized voice actors who consistently dub specific international actors\n\n3. Consistent Voice Actors:\n- In many countries, the same voice actor is assigned to a specific foreign actor\n- These voice actors become closely associated with that actor's persona\n- They continue dubbing the same actor's movies throughout their career\n- This creates a sense of familiarity for the audience\n\n4. Technical Process:\n- Dubbers watch the original film and synchronize their voices with the actors' lip movements\n- They use special recording techniques to match dialogue timing\n- Sound engineers help blend the new audio with the original soundtrack\n\n5. Voice Actor Training:\n- Many voice actors specialize in dubbing and develop skills to match different actors' voices\n- They undergo extensive training in voice modulation and acting\n\nThis process ensures a seamless and natural dubbing experience for viewers in different languages.",
